  "prompt": "Is the scheme of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in most countries around the world. It is a financial crime that involves disguising the origins of money obtained through illegal activities, making it appear as if the funds came from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legal and usable\n\nMoney laundering is a serious criminal offense that can result in significant legal consequences, including:\n- Heavy fines\n- Prison sentences\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nMost countries have strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to prevent and punish such activities.",
